    <p>Brian Hafner Tech is committed to making brianhafner.com accessible to as many people as possible, including people with disabilities.</p>

    <h2>Our goal</h2>
    <p>I aim for this Site to conform to the Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.1 at Level AA. These guidelines explain how to make web content more accessible for people with a wide range of disabilities, including visual, auditory, physical, cognitive, and neurological conditions.</p>

    <h2>Ongoing improvements</h2>
    <p>Accessibility is an ongoing effort. As this Site evolves, I continue to review and improve elements such as color contrast, keyboard navigation, semantic structure, and form labeling to better meet accessibility standards.</p>

    <h2>Feedback and contact</h2>
    <p>If you encounter any accessibility barriers while using this Site, please let me know. I want to hear about it so I can address the issue. You can reach me at <a href="mailto:bh@brianhafner.com">bh@brianhafner.com</a>.</p>

  </div>
</section>

